<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="24" pageNumber="23">
Taxonomic research on recent Polypteridae in the last few decades has been limited to a revision of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BBE9018A-D1F0-438C-BB44-392CCBA05333" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus palmas Ayres 1850:241" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palmas">Polypterus palmas</taxonomicName>
subspecies-complex (Gosse, 1988; Hanssens et al., 1995) and the very recent description of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:850E8201-2A58-4BD9-9467-B6E059B078FD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus teugelsi Britz 2004:180" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="teugelsi">Polypterus teugelsi</taxonomicName>
from the upper Cross River drainage in Cameroon by Britz (2004). The last author concluded that “The discovery of the unusual 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:850E8201-2A58-4BD9-9467-B6E059B078FD" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus teugelsi Britz 2004:180" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="teugelsi">P. teugelsi</taxonomicName>
exemplifies our incomplete taxonomic knowledge of polypterids, and highlights the need for a thorough systematic revision of the genus, which will, I believe, yield additional undescribed species in this interesting group of fishes”. This conclusion is supported by the diversity of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B865A005-F1DE-4C23-BA3D-BFD3804C517A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus Lacépède 1803:340" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Polypterus</taxonomicName>
phenotypes encountered in commercial aquarium imports (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schäfer">Schaefer</normalizedToken>
, 2004). Inspection of hundreds of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B865A005-F1DE-4C23-BA3D-BFD3804C517A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus Lacépède 1803:340" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Polypterus</taxonomicName>
specimens imported through Kinshasa (Democratic Republic of Congo) has resulted in recognition of a presumably undescribed species of this genus that has become known as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sp. &quot;congo&quot;">Polypterus sp. “Congo”</taxonomicName>
in the aquarium trade (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schäfer">Schaefer</normalizedToken>
, 2004). However, during preparation of this manuscript, examination of the three type specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:15A4DA97-CDA9-41AC-9BB5-DA878D0BFFD9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus retropinnis Vaillant 1899:219 [1]" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="retropinnis">Polypterus retropinnis Vaillant, 1899</taxonomicName>
revealed that one of these, listed in Bertin's (1940: 247) type catalogue as the “holotype” of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:15A4DA97-CDA9-41AC-9BB5-DA878D0BFFD9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus retropinnis Vaillant 1899:219 [1]" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="retropinnis">P. retropinnis</taxonomicName>
(MNHN 1886-295), actually is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sp. &quot;congo&quot;">Polypterus sp. “Congo”</taxonomicName>
. The two remaining types (MNHN 1886-297 and BMNH 1907.12.3.4) represent a different species, which is described in the present paper. Inasmuch as the type series of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:15A4DA97-CDA9-41AC-9BB5-DA878D0BFFD9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus retropinnis Vaillant 1899:219 [1]" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="retropinnis">Polypterus retropinnis Vaillant, 1899</taxonomicName>
includes two species, a lectotype is designated for 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:15A4DA97-CDA9-41AC-9BB5-DA878D0BFFD9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Polypteridae" genus="Polypterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Polypterus retropinnis Vaillant 1899:219 [1]" order="Polypteriformes" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="retropinnis">P. retropinnis</taxonomicName>
and a rediagnosis of that species is provided.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
